✅ Customizing Messages for Different Errors

Now, we will dynamically change the "issue" message in error responses based on the type of exception.

1️⃣ Updated extractInputFields Method

This method will:
✔ Customize messages for 400, 404, and 500 errors.
✔ Dynamically update "issue" messages based on failure type.
✔ Handle unexpected cases with fallback messages.

private List<ErrorDetailDTO> extractInputFields(HttpStatus status) {
    List<ErrorDetailDTO> errors = new ArrayList<>();
    String inputFieldsStr = MDC.get("inputFields");

    if (inputFieldsStr != null) {
        try {
            Map<String, Object> inputFields = objectMapper.readValue(inputFieldsStr, Map.class);
            String message = getErrorMessageForStatus(status);

            for (Map.Entry<String, Object> entry : inputFields.entrySet()) {
                errors.add(new ErrorDetailDTO(entry.getKey(), message));
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            errors.add(new ErrorDetailDTO("Parsing Error", "Could not parse request fields"));
        }
    }
    return errors;
}

/**
 * Returns a customized error message based on the HTTP status code.
 */
private String getErrorMessageForStatus(HttpStatus status) {
    if (status == HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST) {
        return "Invalid input provided";
    } else if (status == HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND) {
        return "No results found for this value";
    } else if (status == HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR) {
        return "Query executed but failed";
    }
    return "Processed before failure"; // Fallback message
}

2️⃣ Updated GlobalExceptionHandler

Now, extractInputFields(status) dynamically sets the "issue" field based on the exception type.

@ExceptionHandler(IllegalArgumentException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleIllegalArgumentException(
        IllegalArgumentException ex, HttpServletRequest request) {

    List<ErrorDetailDTO> errors = extractInputFields(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST);

    return buildErrorResponse(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST, ex.getMessage(), errors);
}

@ExceptionHandler(DataNotFoundException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleDataNotFoundException(
        DataNotFoundException ex, HttpServletRequest request) {

    List<ErrorDetailDTO> errors = extractInputFields(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND);

    return buildErrorResponse(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND, ex.getMessage(), errors);
}

@ExceptionHandler(CosmosException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleCosmosException(
        CosmosException ex, HttpServletRequest request) {

    List<ErrorDetailDTO> errors = extractInputFields(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);

    return buildErrorResponse(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, "Database error", errors);
}

